"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Remote collaboration is quite a standard practice in open source projects or online communities.\nIt has gained popularity over the last few years as more and more companies expand their businesses in areas far from the location of the main office (for example, ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"sCffN7jGkX"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.mozilla.org/en-GB/","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mozilla","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"XDyqOpWEap"}],"urlSource":"https://www.mozilla.org/en-GB/","key":"gLJ7bD2z72"},{"type":"text","value":"), or exist entirely as a remote company (for example, ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"EXBaJZIum2"},{"type":"link","url":"https://rstudio.com/about/","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"RStudio","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"sgwoOQNn78"}],"urlSource":"https://rstudio.com/about/","key":"be9GcZacuV"},{"type":"text","value":").","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1},"end":{"line":16,"column":1}},"key":"D7euod6uF7"}],"key":"q9JahqgCeQ"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In early 2020, as we began to work entirely from home due to the ","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"eVZ0n8o3oa"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"PTlxRucwns"}],"urlSource":"https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019","key":"KLqBVZyVQg"},{"type":"text","value":", we experienced a drastic change in our work culture.\nSince 2022, these changes have permanently become part of our work culture, with most people working remotely either fully or partially, with a requirement to go to physical offices for a few days per week or month, or only when necessary.\nThis chapter will present resources and tips for researchers to make their transition of working from the office (physical location) to working from home (online/virtual) easier, or make their collaboration more effective if they are already working remotely.","position":{"start":{"line":19,"column":1},"end":{"line":19,"column":1}},"key":"g8Hy7YC4eV"}],"key":"SESwonXkJQ"},{"type":"comment","value":"- Add a summary of all the subchapters -","key":"xGVkNO7hwR"}],"key":"O38nOPm9Tb"}],"key":"kxP0rXmowy"},"references":{"cite":{"order":["https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3332807"],"data":{"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3332807":{"label":"https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3332807","enumerator":"1","doi":"10.5281/ZENODO.3332807","html":"The Turing Way Community, & Scriberia. (2024). <i>Illustrations from The Turing Way: Shared under CC-BY 4.0 for reuse</i>. Zenodo. <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href=\"https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.3332807\">10.5281/ZENODO.3332807</a>","url":"https://doi.org/10.5281/ZENODO.3332807"}}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Research Infrastructure Developer: Overview","url":"/collaboration/research-infrastructure-roles/research-infrastructure-developer","group":"The Turing Way"},"next":{"title":"Pros and Cons","url":"/collaboration/remote-collab/remote-collab-prosandcons","group":"The Turing Way"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3001"}